# Note: .claude/ is intentionally tracked; it carries spec-governed agent,
# skill, and rule definitions (adopted incrementally from the spec spine).

# Local compliance/audit reports (not for version control)
docs/COMPLIANCE-GAP-REPORT.md

# --- Rust / spec-spine (vendored governance tooling) ---
# Build output
target/
debug/
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Workspace lockfile policy: commit the root Cargo.lock for reproducible CI +
# direct CVE pinning. Member-level lockfiles left by per-manifest cargo
# invocations stay ignored.
Cargo.lock
!/Cargo.lock

# Spec-spine consumer binaries: `make setup` copies the five binaries into
# ./bin/ for the short callsite form. Build artefact, not source; CI and
# contributors regenerate it via `make setup`.
/bin/

# Derived artifacts. The committed .derived/ contents (the spec-registry and
# codebase-index per-spec/per-package shard trees) are produced by `make registry`
# and ARE checked in so the staleness gate has a baseline. build-meta.json is
# ephemeral (carries a wall-clock) and local-only scratch is never committed.
.derived/**/*.tmp
.derived/**/build-meta.json

# Ephemeral produced-app governance evidence, regenerated by the born-with CI
# each run and bound into the emitted certificate (not committed). The corpus
# attestation (OAP spec 220 FR-007) and the per-run certificate directories
# (OAP spec 220 FR-002). The BOM/audit sidecars (.factory/sbom.cdx.json,
# .factory/audit.json) are intentionally left tracked-able so a tenant can opt
# into the committed-sidecar drift gate (OAP spec 203 FR-004).
.derived/attestation/
.factory/runs/

# All env files (incl. .env.github PAT holder); never committable
.env*
!.env.example
!.env.*.example
